<div class="mb-requirement-container">
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15587">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> </span>
      <b>NOTE: </b> The official merit badge pamphlets are now free and
      downloadable
      <a
        href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Pamphlets/Safety.pdf"
        target="_blank"
        >HERE</a
      >
      or can be purchased at the
      <a href="https://www.scoutshop.org/" target="_blank ">Scout Shop.</a>
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15588">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 1. </span>
      <b>Safety and Hazards.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15588 mb-requirement-id-15589">
        (a) Explain what safety is and what it means to be safe. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/qNmd4z2VFAY?si=KG7EvkG4mt08gSxz"
          target="_blank"
          >What is Safety? (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/GRqwuAMqjnY" target="_blank"
          >What Does Safety Mean to You? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15588 mb-requirement-id-15590">
        (b) Explain what hazards are and how people manage hazards to reduce
        risks of harm and to improve safety. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/_GwVTdsnN1E?si=FyaKmgWPC4Hrod-P"
          target="_blank"
          >Hazard and Risk - What's the Difference? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15593">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      <b>Family and Home Safety.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15593 mb-requirement-id-15594">
        (a) Explain common causes of and prevention of home injuries. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://healthtalk.unchealthcare.org/7-common-injuries-that-happen-at-home/"
          target="_blank"
          >Seven Common Home Injuries (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.rubyhome.com/blog/home-accident-stats/"
          target="_blank"
          >Home Accident Statistics (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15593 mb-requirement-id-15595">
        (b) Discuss the dangers involved with the use of fireworks. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/8HxuUMoJyGA?si=bmAF8-rKBe0A1g1v"
          target="_blank"
          >Fireworks Safety (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.mayoclinichealthsystem.org/hometown-health/speaking-of-health/use-caution-with-fireworks"
          target="_blank"
          >Dangers of Fireworks (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15593 mb-requirement-id-15596">
        (c) Explain common causes of and prevention of home fires. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://www.nfpa.org/news-blogs-and-articles/blogs/2020/12/17/most-home-fires-result-from-five-general-causes"
          target="_blank"
          >5 Causes of Home Fires (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15593 mb-requirement-id-15597">
        (d) Using the Home Safety Checklist in the <i>Safety</i> merit badge
        pamphlet, or one approved by your counselor, inspect your home or a
        similar building for hazards with an adult. Review your checklist and
        findings with your counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Emergency%20Preparedness/Home%20Safety%20Checklists%20%231%20%23%202%2001%202026.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Home Safety Checklist (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15593 mb-requirement-id-15598">
        (e) Develop a fire-escape plan for your home or for a similar building.
        Include in your drawings exit routes from each room and a meeting place
        outside. Conduct a fire-escape drill. Review your plan and your drill
        with your counselor. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.nfpa.org/education-and-research/home-fire-safety/escape-planning#safety-tips"
          target="_blank"
          >Home Fire Escape Planning (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zeiN_A-OSt8&amp;t=2s"
          target="_blank"
          >Demonstration of Safely Escaping a House Fire (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15593 mb-requirement-id-15609">
        (f) Develop a family emergency action plan for evacuation because of
        weather or other natural disasters that occur in your area. Using a
        checklist in the <i>Safety</i> merit badge pamphlet or one approved by
        your counselor, assemble or inspect an emergency supplies kit. Explain
        to your counselor how a family would use the plan and the kit supplies
        in an emergency. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Emergency%20Preparedness/Family%20Emergency%20Kit%20Checklist%2001%202026.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Checklist for a Family Emergency Evacuation Kit (PDF)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/EOXSpBkH6zE?si=TgfY5UUhvGwcB8SP"
          target="_blank"
          >Wildfire Evacuation Planning (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/4NbejEMQ6cg" target="_blank"
          >How to Shelter in Place (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.ready.gov/evacuation" target="_blank"
          >Evacuation Planning (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15599">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      <b>Safety from Crime. </b>Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15599 mb-requirement-id-15600">
        (a) Explain common types of crimes that can affect teens.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15599 mb-requirement-id-15601">
        (b) Using a Home Security Checklist in the <i>Safety</i> merit badge
        pamphlet or one approved by your counselor, inspect your home or a
        similar building for crime security measures with an adult. Review your
        checklist and findings with your counselor. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/Merit_Badge_ReqandRes/Requirement%20Resources/Crime%20Prevention/Home%20Security%20Checklists%20%231%20%232.pdf"
          target="_blank"
          >Home Security Checklist (PDF)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15604">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      <b>Safety in Public Places.</b> Explain each of the following to your
      counselor:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15604 mb-requirement-id-15610">
        (a) How a person would safely exit from public buildings, a hotel, and a
        stadium in an emergency. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/KaDcgIx2PlY?si=1EIJSxfDfMlG0AfV"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Survive a Stampede (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/P8Naa4pzDdo?si=5Wr7bMJOmXW9p0XG"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Survive a Burning High Rise (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15604 mb-requirement-id-15611">
        (b) How and why Scouts would take shelter at camp. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/shorts/no3dR86WRss" target="_blank"
          >Camp Emergency Planning (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.acacamps.org/resources/wildfire-evacuations"
          target="_blank"
          >Camp Evacuation Planning (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15604 mb-requirement-id-15612">
        (c) How should Scouts respond to an active shooter. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/sshDd_AgRAA?si=IRhkIwBLtRN6uqjF"
          target="_blank"
          >How to Respond to an Active Shooter (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15604 mb-requirement-id-15613">
        (d) The meaning of this saying: "If You See Something, Say Something.®"
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/Lgm5QWD1T3k?si=ABHK45yx-DqYETJh"
          target="_blank"
          >If You See Something, Say Something® (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15605">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 5. </span>
      <b>Safeguarding Youth.</b> Do the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15605 mb-requirement-id-15614">
        (a) Discuss Scouting America's Safeguarding Youth guidelines that adults
        and Scouts must follow so that everyone is safe at Scouting activities.
        <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://filestore.scouting.org/filestore/YPSAT/YT%20Mod4%20Final%20Master%20Small.mp4"
          target="_blank"
          >Youth Protection Policies (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15605 mb-requirement-id-15615">
        (b) Discuss with your counselor what situations and behaviors would
        prompt you to Recognize, Resist, and Report a possible abuse situation.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15605 mb-requirement-id-15616">
        (c) Discuss how you, other Scouts, leaders, and anyone can report
        situations suspicious for abuse through the Scouts First Helpline and
        other means.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15606">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 6. </span>
      <b> Safety from Assault.</b> Explain how to avoid or prevent:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15606 mb-requirement-id-15617">
        (a) Assault on a street <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/aQdCVTon3HQ" target="_blank"
          >Muggers Reveal How They Target Their Victims (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15606 mb-requirement-id-15618">
        (b) Assault at a restaurant event
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15606 mb-requirement-id-15619">
        (c) Sexual assault at a party or on a date
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15607">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 7. </span>
      <b>Online Safety.</b> Discuss the following with your counselor:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15607 mb-requirement-id-15620">
        (a) How to avoid being the victim of online crimes. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://consumer.ftc.gov/protect-your-personal-information-hackers-scammers#keep"
          target="_blank"
          >Protect Your Personal Information From Hackers and Scammers
          (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/bdp8RdjV6PU?si=MPYq7d0la_3KVSuX"
          target="_blank"
          >Passkeys Explained in Under 4 Minutes (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15607 mb-requirement-id-15621">
        (b) Common online financial scams. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/k8UVnkh8i0c" target="_blank"
          >Common Online Scams (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/CDhAOvsyw2s?si=42nASL5CjtBBKwru"
          target="_blank"
          >10 Common Internet Scams (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15607 mb-requirement-id-15622">
        (c) Effective online security <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/aO858HyFbKI" target="_blank"
          >Effective Online Security (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15607 mb-requirement-id-15623">
        (d) Identity theft and how to prevent it <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/kDFeSUUwRnA?si=ncAfMQF1RIdIWetC"
          target="_blank"
          >Preventing Identity Theft (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15607 mb-requirement-id-15624">
        (e) How criminals use social media to target victims. <br /><i
          >Resource:</i
        >
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/5bdBvNCBeho?si=bJdF2LM50LG_tm74"
          target="_blank"
          >How Criminals Use Social Media (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15607 mb-requirement-id-15625">
        (f) How bullying, texting, and sharing photos can become crimes.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15608">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 8. </span>
      <b>Travel Safety.</b> Explain guidelines for traveling safely:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15608 mb-requirement-id-15626">
        (a) As a pedestrian in a city <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/QUXLT3gcFb8" target="_blank"
          >Pedestrian Safety (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15608 mb-requirement-id-15627">
        (b) In a friend's car or truck <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://www.fmins.com/blog/how-to-be-a-better-passenger/"
          target="_blank"
          >Passenger Responsibilities for Safety (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15608 mb-requirement-id-15628">
        (c) In a rideshare vehicle <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://riskadvisory.ucsf.edu/tips-stay-safe-while-ridesharing"
          target="_blank"
          >Rideshare Safety Tips (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/3ElQynt6rV4?si=ZqpLU9aEY7P2SzLY"
          target="_blank"
          >Ride-Sharing Safety (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15608 mb-requirement-id-15629">
        (d) On a bus <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/fbsDdX7auRo?si=KB3o4EPoNUeZc2xQ"
          target="_blank"
          >Riding a Bus Safely (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://youtu.be/YiI8bnDwkcE" target="_blank"
          >How to Ride a Bus Safely (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15608 mb-requirement-id-15631">
        (e) On a subway or train <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/5w2X_16tuK4" target="_blank"
          >How to Ride a Train Safely (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15608 mb-requirement-id-15630">
        (f) On a commercial airplane <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/vsfudxcksHI" target="_blank"
          >Air Travel Do Not Do's (video)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-15632">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 9. </span>
      <b>Careers.</b> Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15632 mb-requirement-id-15633">
        (a) Explore careers related to Safety merit badge. Research one career
        to learn about the training and education needed, costs, job prospects,
        salary, job duties, and career advancement. With permission of your
        parent or guardian, your research methods may include an internet or
        library search, an interview with a professional in the field, or a
        visit to a location where people in this career work. Discuss with your
        counselor both your findings and what about this profession might make
        it an interesting career. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/zumgPs4PAiA" target="_blank"
          >Wondering How To Get Qualified To Work in Safety?! (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/MT9yVrlSn7M?si=TKjtM1VAhMXmou99"
          target="_blank"
          >Building Safety Careers (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-15632 mb-requirement-id-15634">
        (b) Explore how you could use knowledge and skills related to safety to
        pursue a hobby, lifestyle, or service as a volunteer. Research any
        training needed, expenses, and organizations that promote or support it.
        Discuss with your counselor what short-term and long-term goals you
        might have if you pursue this. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://youtu.be/SfFb2D-3H2s" target="_blank"
          >Volunteers in Mountain Rescue (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/ZlgAJHEWmeg?si=-sKGTI3ErflGOuA_"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety Tips for Serving as Park Volunteer (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.iloveit.net/passion/safety-as-a-passion-and-hobby/"
          target="_blank"
          >Safety as a Passion (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
</div>
